KW  - Goodness-of-fit
KW  - Linear processes
KW  - Spectral distribution
KW  - Gaussian processes
KW  - Bootstrap tests
AB  - This paper discusses goodness-of-fit tests for linear covariance stationary processes based on the empirical spectral distribution function. We can show that the limiting distribution of the tests are functionals of a Gaussian process, say, B˜(ϑ) with ϑ∈[0,1]. Since in general it is not easy, if at all possible, to find a time deformation g(ϑ) such that B˜(g(ϑ)) is a Brownian (bridge) process, tests based on B˜(ϑ) will have limited value for the purpose of statistical inference. To circumvent the problem, we propose to bootstrap the test showing its validity. We also provide a Monte-Carlo experiment to examine the finite sample behaviour of the bootstrap.
ER  - 

